WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.838
[adventurous music]

00:04.921 --> 00:12.929
♪ ♪

00:32.198 --> 00:34.242
[alarm rings]

00:39.622 --> 00:42.500
- MORNING.

00:42.584 --> 00:45.837
- MORNING.

00:45.920 --> 00:48.548
I JUST HAD THE WEIRDEST DREAM.

00:48.631 --> 00:50.008
- ME TOO.

00:50.091 --> 00:52.969
I WAS A PERSONAL SHOPPER
FOR LADY GAGA,

00:53.052 --> 00:54.512
AND SHE TIPPED ME IN SALAMI.

00:54.596 --> 00:55.680
- [laughs]

00:55.764 --> 00:56.931
- WHAT WAS YOURS?

00:58.850 --> 01:00.310
- I CAN'T REMEMBER.

01:07.233 --> 01:10.153
- SO YOU TOOK THIS CUP
DOWNSTAIRS

01:10.236 --> 01:12.572
AFTER SEEING THIS GHOST
OR WHATEVER.

01:12.655 --> 01:15.742
- YEAH, AND THE NEXT THING
I REMEMBER WAS MY ALARM.

01:15.825 --> 01:18.703
- IT MUST HAVE BEEN A DREAM,
BUT IT FELT SO REAL.

01:18.787 --> 01:20.288
- [whispering indistinctly]
AS IT WAS CHOSEN.

01:22.749 --> 01:25.543
- LET'S GO GET BREAKFAST,
LIKE, RIGHT NOW.

01:25.627 --> 01:26.628
- BUT...

01:28.880 --> 01:31.466
- MICK.

01:31.549 --> 01:33.259
- WANT TO WALK OVER?

01:33.343 --> 01:34.761
- ARE YOU INSANE?

01:34.844 --> 01:36.888
LOOK, I'M NOT INTERESTED, OKAY?

01:36.971 --> 01:39.307
DAD,
WE SPOKE ABOUT THIS.

01:39.390 --> 01:40.892
I'M NOT OKAY WITH IT.

01:40.975 --> 01:42.143
OH, SORRY, GORGEOUS.

01:42.227 --> 01:44.270
I'M JUST IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

01:44.354 --> 01:45.605
NO, NOT YOU, DAD.

01:45.688 --> 01:47.440
LOOK, LISTEN.

01:47.524 --> 01:49.025
LISTEN.

01:49.108 --> 01:51.194
I'LL CALL YOU LATER, OKAY?

01:51.986 --> 01:55.824
I'M GOING FOR A RUN.

01:58.243 --> 02:01.204
- DID ANYBODY HEAR THAT
TERRIBLE NOISE IN THE NIGHT?

02:01.287 --> 02:03.748
SOUNDED LIKE A WOOLLY MAMMOTH
WITH HEARTBURN.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.501
- [whispers]
IT'S GRAN.

02:06.584 --> 02:08.211
[laughs]

02:08.294 --> 02:08.836
- YOU WANT TO HEAD OVER
TOGETHER?

02:08.919 --> 02:13.383
- MM...I MEAN, NO.

02:13.466 --> 02:14.300
MAYBE?

02:14.384 --> 02:15.218
- DECISIVE AS EVER.

02:15.301 --> 02:16.553
- I'LL JUST GET MY BAG, FABES.

02:16.636 --> 02:18.888
- WHAT?

02:18.972 --> 02:20.139
- HEY, SO I'LL GET MY BAG,

02:20.223 --> 02:21.599
AND WE'LL WALK ACROSS TOGETHER,
OKAY?

02:21.683 --> 02:24.894
- UH...

02:24.978 --> 02:29.649
- MAY I GIVE YOU A WORD
OF ADVICE, FABIAN?

02:29.732 --> 02:31.150
ASSERTIVENESS.

02:31.234 --> 02:33.236
GIRLS KNOW WHAT THEY WANT,

02:33.319 --> 02:35.822
AND THAT'S BOYS WHO KNOW
WHAT THEY WANT.

02:35.905 --> 02:36.948
- RIGHT.

02:37.031 --> 02:38.408
- THEY LIKE SOULFULNESS TOO,

02:38.491 --> 02:42.245
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO BE
ASSERTIVE ENOUGH TO SHOW IT.

02:42.328 --> 02:43.079
- RIGHT.

02:43.162 --> 02:45.164
- DID YOU KNOW I WRITE POETRY?

02:45.248 --> 02:48.835
- OH, NINA MIGHT HAVE
MENTIONED THAT.

02:48.918 --> 02:51.087
- WRITE A POEM FOR NINA.

02:51.170 --> 02:52.964
I'LL HELP YOU.

02:53.047 --> 02:57.176
AND NO NEED TO THANK ME.

03:06.311 --> 03:09.272
[dramatic music]

03:09.355 --> 03:11.608
♪ ♪

03:11.691 --> 03:15.111
- YOU HAVE FREED ME,
CHOSEN ONE.

03:15.194 --> 03:18.072
FIND IT,
THE MASK OF ANUBIS, CHILD,

03:18.156 --> 03:19.407
OR FORFEIT YOUR LIFE.

03:28.374 --> 03:31.586
- IT WASN'T A DREAM.

03:31.669 --> 03:33.463
LOOK.

03:33.546 --> 03:34.672
IT WAS UNDER MY BED.

03:34.756 --> 03:36.215
- MAYBE YOU WERE SLEEPWALKING.

03:36.299 --> 03:37.842
- SLEEPWALKING?

03:37.926 --> 03:39.135
SHE MENTIONED TEARS OF GOLD,

03:39.218 --> 03:40.637
JUST LIKE IN THE DREAM
WITH VICTOR

03:40.720 --> 03:41.804
AND JUST LIKE THE DOLL SAID.

03:41.888 --> 03:43.348
OKAY, SURELY IT CAN'T BE
A COINCIDENCE.

03:43.431 --> 03:46.851
- MAYBE YOU DREAMT IT
BECAUSE HEARD THE DOLL SAY IT.

03:46.935 --> 03:48.311
I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO BE LATE TODAY.

03:48.394 --> 03:49.646
- ARE YOU READY, FABES?

04:00.114 --> 04:02.659
- LET'S ALL WALK OVER TOGETHER,
SHALL WE?

04:02.742 --> 04:04.953
- PERFECT...

04:05.036 --> 04:06.663
ALL THREE OF US,
FINALLY.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.831
- [chuckles]

04:14.295 --> 04:16.130
- HERE,
I NEED YOU TO TAKE SOME PHOTOS.

04:18.882 --> 04:20.969
- OKAY,
BECAUSE THIS ISN'T WEIRD AT ALL.

04:21.052 --> 04:22.929
- LOOK, IF I'M GONNA BE
AMBER'S BOYFRIEND,

04:23.012 --> 04:24.514
I NEED TO GET MY FACE
ON A NEWSSTAND

04:24.597 --> 04:25.306
WITHOUT GETTING THROWN OFF
A TRAIN

04:25.390 --> 04:27.767
OR KICKED OFF SOME TALENT SHOW.

04:27.850 --> 04:31.854
- SO ARE YOU GOING TO TELL ME
WHAT WAS GOING ON AT HOME?

04:31.938 --> 04:33.106
IT CAN'T BE THAT BAD,
CAN IT?

04:33.189 --> 04:35.108
- THEY'RE RELOCATING

04:35.191 --> 04:39.570
MY WHOLE FAMILY TO AUSTRALIA.

04:39.654 --> 04:42.865
- AUSTRALIA?

04:42.949 --> 04:45.451
OKAY, THAT IS BAD.

04:45.535 --> 04:47.704
- SORRY, I MEAN, IT'S BIG.

04:47.787 --> 04:49.580
- THEY WANT ME TO JOIN
A NEW SCHOOL OVER THERE,

04:49.664 --> 04:53.126
BUT I'VE TOLD THEM
I'M STAYING HERE.

04:53.209 --> 04:54.085
- OH, GOOD.

04:54.168 --> 04:57.088
- I MEAN, ARE YOU SURE?

04:57.171 --> 04:58.548
- THIS IS HOME.

04:58.631 --> 05:01.801
I ONLY REALLY SEE THEM
AT SCHOOL HOLIDAYS, ANYWAY,

05:01.884 --> 05:03.886
SO WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

05:10.101 --> 05:13.521
- I LIKE HIM MORE NOW THAN EVER.

05:13.604 --> 05:15.565
DO YOU THINK IT'S BECAUSE
HE'S TAKEN?

05:15.648 --> 05:17.817
- YEAH, MAYBE.

05:17.900 --> 05:19.152
- DOES THAT MAKE ME
A BAD PERSON?

05:19.235 --> 05:22.113
SHOULD I TELL HIM HOW I FEEL?

05:22.196 --> 05:24.907
- YEAH...MAYBE.

05:24.991 --> 05:25.742
- YOU'RE NOT LISTENING.

05:25.825 --> 05:28.494
- SORRY, JOY.

05:28.578 --> 05:31.581
BOY TALK AFTER A FEW MINUTES,
IT JUST SOUND LIKE NOISE.

05:31.664 --> 05:34.125
- WHAT DOES HE SEE
IN HER ANYWAY,

05:34.208 --> 05:38.755
EXCEPT SHE'S REALLY PRETTY.

05:38.838 --> 05:42.925
- AND ALSO A KIND OF
MYSTICAL CHAMPION OF GOOD.

05:43.009 --> 05:43.926
SORRY.

05:44.010 --> 05:47.430
I MEAN,
THEY JUST HAVE A LOT IN COMMON.

05:47.513 --> 05:50.016
- YEAH, WELL, FROM NOW ON,

05:50.099 --> 05:51.976
I'LL HAVE A LOT IN COMMON
WITH FABES TOO.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.978
- [groans]

05:54.062 --> 05:55.938
- AND WORK IT.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.106
WORK IT.
HOLD IT.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.942
GIVE ME A LITTLE TIGER GROWL.

06:00.026 --> 06:00.651
YES, YES, THAT'S IT.

06:00.735 --> 06:01.694
THAT'S IT, EXACTLY.

06:01.778 --> 06:02.904
NOW,
GIVE ME A LITTLE HUNGRY EYES.

06:02.987 --> 06:05.114
AND POSE, POSE.

06:05.198 --> 06:06.240
YES, ALFIE.

06:06.324 --> 06:10.286
FLEX IT UP,
AND KICK OUT.

06:10.369 --> 06:12.455
KICK.

06:12.538 --> 06:14.540
THAT WAS THE BEST POSE EVER.

06:14.624 --> 06:17.376
- WAS THERE ANY MENTION
FROM VICTOR'S DOLL

06:17.460 --> 06:18.503
ABOUT A MASK OF ANUBIS?

06:18.586 --> 06:23.800
- NO, BUT JUST THIS
TEARS OF GOLD AGAIN.

06:23.883 --> 06:26.135
DO YOU THINK THE TWO ARE LINKED?

06:26.219 --> 06:29.555
- BEFORE WE BEGIN BIOLOGY,

06:29.639 --> 06:33.101
I HAVE AN IMPORTANT
ANNOUNCEMENT.

06:34.769 --> 06:37.313
WE HAVE BEEN ASKED TO PRESENT
AN OFFICIAL BID

06:37.396 --> 06:41.150
TO HOST
A PRESTIGIOUS EXHIBITION.

06:41.234 --> 06:44.195
- YES,
THE TOURING TREASURES OF EGYPT.

06:44.278 --> 06:47.824
IT IS ABSOLUTELY IMPERATIVE
THAT WE WIN.

06:47.907 --> 06:51.494
- SO I NEED VOLUNTEERS
TO HELP US PREPARE THE BID.

06:51.577 --> 06:53.412
MARA, FABIAN, EXCELLENT.

06:53.496 --> 06:56.249
IDEALLY,
I'D LIKE THREE FROM EACH CLASS,

06:56.332 --> 06:57.166
SO ONE...JOY, PERFECT.

06:57.250 --> 07:00.837
AND THERE'S MY THREE.

07:02.672 --> 07:05.174
- WE MAKE A GOOD TEAM,
DON'T WE, FABES.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.927
MUST BE ALL THAT STUFF
WE HAVE IN COMMON.

07:08.010 --> 07:10.054
- FIRST MEETING:
5:00 THIS AFTERNOON,

07:10.138 --> 07:12.682
FROBISHER LIBRARY.

07:12.765 --> 07:16.018
THANK YOU.

07:16.102 --> 07:19.355
- THERE'S DEFINITELY SOMETHING
VICTOR WANTS AT THAT EXHIBITION.

07:19.438 --> 07:22.233
I NEED TO GET ON THAT TEAM.

07:22.316 --> 07:24.235
- AND I KNOW YOU ALREADY HAVE
ALL YOUR VOLUNTEERS,

07:24.318 --> 07:27.155
BUT EGYPTIAN HISTORY
IS A REAL PASSION OF MINE,

07:27.238 --> 07:28.322
AND I'LL PUT ALL THE HOURS IN,

07:28.406 --> 07:30.366
AND OUR EGYPTIAN PLAY LAST TERM
WAS SOLD OUT,

07:30.449 --> 07:30.992
AND I WAS THINKING OF WRITING
A SEQUEL--

07:31.075 --> 07:32.368
- I ACCEPT.

07:32.451 --> 07:35.705
OR SHOULD THAT BE,
I SURRENDER?

07:35.788 --> 07:37.915
I'LL SEE YOU
IN THE MEETING LATER.

07:37.999 --> 07:38.624
- THANK YOU.

07:55.683 --> 07:57.935
- YAY,
THAT'S ALL MY PICS SENT OUT.

07:58.019 --> 07:59.187
NOW I JUST NEED
TO SIT BACK AND WAIT

07:59.270 --> 08:00.438
FOR THE GLOSSY OFFERS TO ROLL IN

08:00.521 --> 08:03.608
- ROBERT PATTINSON MUST BE
QUAKING IN HIS BOOTS.

08:03.691 --> 08:06.068
- ENOUGH ALREADY.

08:06.152 --> 08:06.944
- NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, NO.

08:07.028 --> 08:09.655
MARA...NO.

08:09.739 --> 08:11.240
- WHAT DID THEY SAY?

08:11.324 --> 08:13.409
- MOM WANTS TO TAKE ME OUT
FOR THE DAY TOMORROW,

08:13.492 --> 08:15.036
YOU KNOW, SAY GOOD-BYE
BEFORE THEY FLY OFF,

08:15.119 --> 08:16.621
BUT I'VE GOT TO CLEAR IT
WITH TRUDY.

08:21.083 --> 08:23.294
- ENOUGH, ALREADY.

08:23.377 --> 08:26.964
- THE BED.

08:33.386 --> 08:35.431
- WE MUST BE THE FIRST PEOPLE
TO SET FOOT

08:35.514 --> 08:38.183
IN FROBISHER LIBRARY
FOR DECADES.

08:38.267 --> 08:39.559
- YEAH?

08:39.644 --> 08:42.605
JOY,
DO YOU THINK I'M A PUSHOVER?

08:46.692 --> 08:48.736
- NINA'S GRAN THINK I NEED
TO STEP UP MY GAME,

08:48.819 --> 08:53.616
AND I DIDN'T REALIZE I HAD
A GAME TO STEP UP.

08:53.699 --> 08:57.954
- WELL, IF YOU EVER NEED TO,
WELL, YOU KNOW,

08:58.037 --> 08:59.997
PRACTICE YOUR CHAT-UP SKILLS,

09:00.081 --> 09:00.790
YOU CAN ALWAYS PRACTICE THEM
ON ME.

09:00.873 --> 09:03.125
- OH...

09:03.209 --> 09:04.502
- [silently]

09:04.585 --> 09:06.462
- OH, THANK YOU, EVERYBODY.

09:06.545 --> 09:11.133
WELL, THIS IS WHERE WE PROPOSED
TO HOST THE EXHIBITION.

09:11.217 --> 09:13.469
NEEDS A LITTLE BIT OF WORK,
OF COURSE.

09:13.552 --> 09:16.889
NOW, I WAS THINKING ALONG
THE LINES OF PHOTOGRAPHS

09:16.973 --> 09:19.058
AND A SPEECH ABOUT THE HISTORY
OF THE LIBRARY

09:19.141 --> 09:21.978
AND THE ESTATE, HMM?

09:22.061 --> 09:23.980
- SHOULDN'T IT BE SOMETHING
MORE DYNAMIC, MR. SWEET,

09:24.063 --> 09:25.815
LIKE A FILM?

09:25.898 --> 09:28.234
- OH, NO; WE HAVEN'T GOT THE
MONEY FOR THAT KIND OF THING.

09:28.317 --> 09:31.112
- I'M SURE WE CAN REALLOCATE
SOME MONEY FROM SOMEWHERE.

09:31.195 --> 09:35.324
- WELL...YES.

09:35.408 --> 09:40.121
IS SUPPOSE A MOVIE
IS QUITE A GOOD IDEA.

09:40.204 --> 09:42.206
both: SORRY.
SORRY WE'RE LATE, MR. SWEET.

09:42.290 --> 09:45.167
- IF YOU CANNOT TURN UP ON TIME,
YOU MAY AS WELL GO NOW.

09:45.251 --> 09:49.297
WE MUST WIN THIS BID.

09:49.380 --> 09:51.674
I DEMAND TOTAL COMMITMENT.

09:57.805 --> 10:01.600
- WASN'T IT THREE VOLUNTEERS
PER CLASS?

10:01.684 --> 10:03.686
- I DON'T REMEMBER YOU
VOLUNTEERING, NINA.

10:03.769 --> 10:05.187
- NO, NEITHER DO I.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.856
YOU MAY GO, MISS MARTIN.

10:06.939 --> 10:07.857
- NINA...

10:07.940 --> 10:09.150
SHE SHOULD STAY, VICTOR.

10:09.233 --> 10:13.696
SHE REALLY KNOWS HER STUFF
ON EGYPTIAN HISTORY.

10:13.779 --> 10:14.989
IT'S ALL RIGHT, NINA.

10:15.072 --> 10:15.531
YOU CAN STAY.

10:15.615 --> 10:18.159
- [silently]

10:23.956 --> 10:27.626
- HEY, LOOK WHAT I MANAGED
TO PERSUADE SWEETIE TO LEND US.

10:27.710 --> 10:29.879
IT CONTAINS EVERY ITEM
IN THE EXPO,

10:29.962 --> 10:31.047
SO MAYBE WE CAN FIND
WHAT VICTOR'S INTERESTED IN.

10:31.130 --> 10:34.050
- NICE.

10:34.133 --> 10:36.552
- ARE YOU STILL CARRYING
THE CUP AROUND?

10:36.635 --> 10:39.138
- NO, I MANAGED TO PUT IT BACK
IN THE ATTIC.

10:39.221 --> 10:43.642
SAFER THERE.

10:43.726 --> 10:46.562
FABIAN,
LOOK AT THIS.

10:46.645 --> 10:48.439
"THE MASK OF ANUBIS
WAS A MYTHICAL MASK

10:48.522 --> 10:50.733
"WORN BY THE HIGH PRIEST
OF NUBIS,

10:50.816 --> 10:52.902
"GOD OF DEATH.

10:52.985 --> 10:55.905
"LEGEND HAS IT THAT WHEN WORN
AT THE FUNERAL PHARAOHS,

10:55.988 --> 10:58.949
THE MASK USED TO WEEP
TEARS OF GOLD."

10:59.033 --> 10:59.992
NOW DO YOU BELIEVE ME?

11:00.076 --> 11:03.287
HOW COULD I HAVE KNOWN
ANY OF THIS?

11:03.371 --> 11:04.330
IF VICTOR'S AFTER TEARS OF GOLD,

11:04.413 --> 11:05.539
THAT MEANS HE NEEDS
THE MASK TOO.

11:05.623 --> 11:07.249
- [whispers]
CHOSEN ONE.

11:07.333 --> 11:09.543
CHOSEN ONE.

11:09.627 --> 11:10.086
FIND IT.

11:10.169 --> 11:11.087
FIND IT.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.422
- WHAT IS IT?

11:13.506 --> 11:15.758
WHAT'S WRONG?

11:15.841 --> 11:16.592
- IT'S ME AGAINST VICTOR,
FABIAN.

11:16.675 --> 11:20.679
MY LIFE REALLY IS IN DANGER.

11:29.730 --> 11:31.982
- EGGS COMING UP, GRAN,
OVER EASY--

11:32.066 --> 11:33.275
- OVER EASY, PLEA...

11:33.359 --> 11:34.568
[laughter]

11:34.652 --> 11:35.986
- HEY, MORNING.

11:36.070 --> 11:38.364
I WAS LOOKING THROUGH THIS
EXHIBITION CATALOG LAST NIGHT.,

11:38.447 --> 11:40.950
AND YOU WILL NOT BELIEVE
WHAT I FOUND.

11:42.868 --> 11:44.286
- THE MASK OF ANUBIS.

11:44.370 --> 11:46.872
- IT'S A REPLICA, BUT
YOU'LL NEVER GUESS WHO MADE IT.

11:46.956 --> 11:49.959
- "BRONZE REPLICA
OF THE GOLDEN MASK OF ANUBIS

11:50.042 --> 11:52.420
ARTIST:
LOUISA FROBISHER-SMYTHE."

11:52.503 --> 11:53.295
SARAH'S MOTHER.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.923
- WHAT IS THAT?

11:56.006 --> 11:58.217
- OH,
IT'S AN EXHIBITION CATALOG.

11:58.300 --> 12:00.261
MR. SWEET GAVE IT TO US
AS RESEARCH FOR THE BID.

12:00.344 --> 12:03.305
- GIVE IT TO ME.
- OH, UM...

12:07.226 --> 12:10.980
UH...OH,
I'LL NEED IT BACK.

12:11.063 --> 12:12.648
THAT WAS THE ONLY COPY.

12:12.731 --> 12:14.525
WHY DID I LET HIM TAKE IT?

12:14.608 --> 12:15.693
YOUR GRAN IS RIGHT.

12:15.776 --> 12:16.819
I'M JUST A TOTAL PUSHOVER.

12:16.902 --> 12:18.195
- HEY.

12:19.447 --> 12:21.323
- WRITTEN YOUR POEM YET,
FABIAN?

12:21.407 --> 12:22.700
- YEAH, YEAH, OF COURSE.

12:22.783 --> 12:25.786
- AFTER SCHOOL:
ASSERTIVENESS 101.

12:25.870 --> 12:26.829
BRING THE POEM.

12:26.912 --> 12:29.874
- SOUNDS GREAT.

12:29.957 --> 12:31.834
[mumbles]

12:31.917 --> 12:35.463
- OH,
I'M OFF TO SEE MY FOLKS NOW,

12:35.546 --> 12:37.840
SO I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

12:37.923 --> 12:39.842
- GOOD LUCK.

12:39.925 --> 12:42.470
- WHY IS MICK GOING
TO SEE HIS FAMILY

12:42.553 --> 12:43.679
SO SOON AFTER THE HOLIDAYS?

12:43.762 --> 12:48.267
- GOT HIS BLANKIE?

12:48.350 --> 12:50.769
HIS FAMILY IS RELOCATING
TO AUSTRALIA.

12:50.853 --> 12:53.022
- AND MICK'S NOT GOING
WITH THEM?

12:53.105 --> 12:54.148
- NO WAY.

12:54.231 --> 12:56.358
HE WANTS TO STAY HERE.

12:56.442 --> 12:57.860
HE'S TELLING THEM TODAY.

12:57.943 --> 13:00.362
- JOCKS AND CROCS.

13:00.446 --> 13:05.284
I'LL BE OVER THERE LIKE A SHOT.

13:05.367 --> 13:07.077
THEN AGAIN...

13:08.704 --> 13:09.997
- HEY, JEROME.

13:10.080 --> 13:12.041
I GOT SOME RESPONSES TO THE PICS
I SENT OUT YESTERDAY.

13:12.124 --> 13:13.250
- RIGHT.

13:13.334 --> 13:17.755
- OH, IT'S A NO...
NO...

13:17.838 --> 13:19.423
ANOTHER NO.

13:19.507 --> 13:20.299
OH, YES.

13:20.382 --> 13:24.595
"WE GOT YOUR EMAIL,
AND..."

13:24.678 --> 13:25.638
NO.

13:25.721 --> 13:26.972
- [laughs]

13:27.056 --> 13:29.016
ALFIE, MAYBE YOU NEED TO GO
A LITTLE BIT NICHE.

13:29.099 --> 13:30.893
AMBER NEVER SAID
WHAT TYPE OF MAGAZINE.

13:30.976 --> 13:35.022
SET THE BAR NICE AND LOW.

14:06.095 --> 14:08.973
- GET YOUR STICKY MITTS
OFF MY STUFF NOW.

14:09.056 --> 14:10.599
AND NO,
YOU CAN'T HAVE YOUR PHONE BACK.

14:10.683 --> 14:14.103
- HOW LONG HAVE YOU HAD THIS?

14:14.186 --> 14:16.939
IT'S FROM DAD, ISN'T IT?

14:17.022 --> 14:19.316
IT'S OKAY FOR YOU.
YOU CAN REMEMBER HIM.

14:19.400 --> 14:21.110
I CAN'T.

14:21.193 --> 14:22.695
- ALL MY MEMORIES ARE BAD.

14:22.778 --> 14:24.238
- OH,
CHANGE THE RECORD, GERBIL.

14:24.321 --> 14:26.574
NOBODY'S ALL BAD.

14:26.657 --> 14:27.866
- EEE-AHH, WRONG.

14:27.950 --> 14:28.409
- I HAVEN'T READ IT YET.

14:28.492 --> 14:30.786
- TRUST ME.

14:30.869 --> 14:34.373
YOU ARE NOT GOING TO FEEL
ANY BETTER ONCE YOU HAVE.

14:35.708 --> 14:38.419
- FINE,
TAKE YOUR PHONE AND QUIT

14:38.502 --> 14:39.712
WHILST YOU ARE AHEAD,
OKAY?

14:39.795 --> 14:42.881
OUT.

14:49.888 --> 14:52.808
- AHH, SO, NINA, YOU'RE DOWN
TO WRITE THE FILM SCRIPT.

14:52.891 --> 14:54.685
THAT'S KIND OF YOUR THING,
RIGHT?

14:54.768 --> 14:56.687
FABES AND I ARE DIRECTOR
AND CAMERA OPERATOR,

14:56.770 --> 14:58.522
AND THE CAMERA SHOULD BE
ARRIVING THIS EVENING.

14:58.606 --> 15:02.276
- SOUND LIKE YOU TWO WILL BE
SPENDING A LOT OF TIME TOGETHER.

15:02.359 --> 15:04.903
- WHILE THE WRITER IS STUCK
ALONE IN HER ROOM.

15:08.741 --> 15:13.078
YEAH, WELL, THINK AGAIN, SISTER.

15:13.162 --> 15:14.038
- GO, NINA.

15:14.121 --> 15:15.664
- IT'S SO OBVIOUS SHE LIKES HIM.

15:15.748 --> 15:16.999
- YOU DON'T SAY.

15:17.082 --> 15:18.751
QUESTION IS, DO YOU?

15:18.834 --> 15:20.252
- WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

15:20.336 --> 15:24.757
- OKAY, LAST TIME, YOU AND
FABIAN WERE, LIKE, BEST FRIENDS,

15:24.840 --> 15:26.550
AND THIS TIME, YOU'RE, LIKE...

15:26.634 --> 15:27.593
- BEST FRIENDS.

15:27.676 --> 15:29.094
- THOUGHT SO.

15:29.178 --> 15:33.223
YOU TWO NEED SOME SERIOUS
DAVINA TIME.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.143
LEAVE IT WITH ME.

15:39.730 --> 15:42.691
[dramatic music]

15:42.775 --> 15:46.362
♪ ♪

15:46.445 --> 15:48.947
- HAD IT THE WHOLE TIME
AND DIDN'T THINK TO TELL ME?

15:49.031 --> 15:51.867
- JUST A CATALOG
THAT GUSTAV GAVE ME,

15:51.950 --> 15:54.620
AND THE FABIAN NEEDED IT
TO RESEARCH THE BID.

15:54.703 --> 15:56.747
- WHAT ABOUT MY RESEARCH?

15:56.830 --> 16:00.959
EVERY SINGLE EXHIBIT IS LISTED
IN THIS CATALOG, ERIC.

16:01.043 --> 16:02.294
- AND THE BOOK OF ISIS?

16:02.378 --> 16:05.756
- THE BOOK OF ISIS.

16:05.839 --> 16:06.256
- IS NOT MENTIONED.

16:06.340 --> 16:08.676
- DEAR.

16:08.759 --> 16:11.387
DO WE CONTINUE WITH THE BID?

16:11.470 --> 16:13.263
- OF COURSE.

16:13.347 --> 16:15.349
OF COURSE WE CONTINUE
WITH THE BID.

16:15.432 --> 16:19.269
IT WILL BE SIMPLY CATALOGED
UNDER A CODE NAME.

16:21.689 --> 16:24.233
[school bell rings]

16:24.316 --> 16:27.236
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DELETED
ALL MY PHOTOS.

16:27.319 --> 16:28.362
- I HAD TO TAKE ACTION.

16:28.445 --> 16:29.405
- YOU'RE EVIL.

16:29.488 --> 16:30.823
THOSE PHOTOS ARE MINE.

16:30.906 --> 16:33.617
- WHY DO YOU WANT PHOTOS OF ME
ON YOUR PHONE ANYWAY, POPPY?

16:33.701 --> 16:37.079
- I...LIKE THEM.

16:40.332 --> 16:41.291
- REASON?

16:41.375 --> 16:44.920
- THEY REMIND ME
OF WHEN THEY WERE TAKEN,

16:45.003 --> 16:48.173
LIKE, MY RECITAL.

16:48.257 --> 16:51.510
MUM DODGED IT,
BUT YOU CAME.

16:54.763 --> 16:57.766
- THE PHOTOS ARE STORED
ON MY LAPTOP.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.477
YOU CAN HAVE THEM BACK--
WELL, MOST OF THEM.

17:00.561 --> 17:01.311
- AND WHAT ABOUT THAT LETTER?

17:01.395 --> 17:04.106
- DON'T PUSHY IT, POOPIE.

17:04.189 --> 17:08.109
- HAS HE JUST UPSET YOU?

17:08.193 --> 17:09.278
- HE'S SUCH A MEAN BROTHER.

17:09.361 --> 17:11.113
- WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT HE'S DONE NOW?

17:13.949 --> 17:16.117
- HOW MUCH REJECTION
CAN ONE GUY TAKE?

17:16.201 --> 17:20.329
EVEN THE NICHE GEEKS
ARE SAYING NO.

17:20.414 --> 17:24.334
- YOU ARE NOTHING BUT
A BIG BULLY, JEROME CLARKE.

17:24.417 --> 17:26.295
- MARA, I DO LOVE IT
WHEN YOU TALK ME UP.

17:26.377 --> 17:28.839
- POPPY JUST WANTS TO READ
THE LETTER.

17:28.922 --> 17:30.299
SHE IS YOUR SISTER.

17:30.382 --> 17:32.384
- SHE'S A ROBOT SENT
FROM THE FUTURE TO RUIN MY LIFE.

17:32.468 --> 17:35.596
- PLEASE.

17:35.679 --> 17:36.972
FOR ME.

17:39.016 --> 17:42.019
- AFRAID I CAN DENY YOU NOTHING.

17:42.102 --> 17:46.148
OKAY, SHE CAN SEE IT,
BUT DO NOT BE TAKEN IN BY HER.

17:46.231 --> 17:48.650
I TRAINED THIS GIRL MYSELF.

17:57.534 --> 18:00.871
- IMAGINE I'M NINA.

18:00.954 --> 18:03.248
- OH, DO I HAVE TO?

18:03.332 --> 18:05.959
- OKAY, IMAGINE THIS CROCODILE
IS NINA.

18:06.043 --> 18:07.336
- THAT'S BETTER.
THANK YOU.

18:07.419 --> 18:12.674
- NOW, TAKE A DEEP BREATH,
AND BEGIN THE POEM.

18:12.758 --> 18:14.802
- "THE QUEST WAS--
WAS LONG AND DIFFICULT."

18:14.885 --> 18:17.346
- SPEAK OUT.
ASSERT YOURSELF.

18:17.429 --> 18:19.681
- "THE QUESTION WAS LONG
AND DIFFICULT.

18:19.765 --> 18:21.934
I SOUGHT TREASURE."

18:22.017 --> 18:25.187
- LOOK HER IN THE EYES.

18:25.270 --> 18:26.814
- "THE TREASURE WAS YOU."

18:26.897 --> 18:28.857
- GOOD, GOOD.
KEEP GOING.

18:28.941 --> 18:30.651
- THAT'S IT.

18:30.734 --> 18:32.027
- HUH?

18:32.110 --> 18:36.824
- WELL, IT--IT'S A HAIKU.

18:36.907 --> 18:39.660
- ONCE MORE...WITH FEELING.

18:39.743 --> 18:40.452
- YES.

18:40.536 --> 18:42.704
YES, FINALLY, SOMEONE WANTS ME.

18:42.788 --> 18:44.039
- NO WAY.

18:44.122 --> 18:45.916
- THEY'VE SENT ME A MOCK-UP
OF MY COVER SHOT.

18:45.999 --> 18:49.044
[knock at door]

18:58.929 --> 19:01.181
- TEN MINUTES,
NO MORE,

19:01.265 --> 19:03.433
OR YOU LOSE YOUR DEPOSIT.

19:16.613 --> 19:18.282
- YOU GOT IT, THEN?

19:20.701 --> 19:24.371
- HE SAYS HE'S SORRY
FOR BEING A HOPELESS DAD.

19:27.958 --> 19:29.835
THERE'S NO ADDRESS ON HERE.

19:29.918 --> 19:31.295
IT'S BEEN TORN OFF.

19:31.378 --> 19:34.423
JEROME, PROBABLY.

19:34.506 --> 19:36.216
BUT LOOK AT THIS.

19:36.300 --> 19:40.387
-<i> "FIAT JUSTITIA RUAT CAELUM."</i>

19:40.470 --> 19:41.805
IT'S LATIN.

19:41.889 --> 19:45.434
"LET JUSTICE BE DONE
THOUGH THE HEAVENS FALL."

19:45.517 --> 19:48.729
- OKAY,
NOW I'M SERIOUSLY IMPRESSED.

19:48.812 --> 19:51.064
- SO MAYBE THIS MEANS
YOUR DAD'S IN LAW.

19:51.148 --> 19:53.108
WE CAN GO LOOK HIM UP ONLINE
IF YOU LIKE.

19:53.192 --> 19:54.276
- I LIKE.

19:54.359 --> 19:56.445
- COVER BOY COMING THROUGH.

19:56.528 --> 19:58.155
HA-HA.

19:59.364 --> 20:01.533
GET READY FOR ANOTHER TICK,
AMBER,

20:01.617 --> 20:05.162
BECAUSE ALFIE GOT HIMSELF
A GLOSSY.

20:05.245 --> 20:06.788
both: UGH.

20:06.872 --> 20:10.208
- WORST CASE OF ATHLETES FOOT
THEY'VE EVER SEEN, APPARENTLY.

20:10.292 --> 20:11.793
YOU NEVER SPECIFIED FACE.

20:11.877 --> 20:13.086
I GOT ON THE COVER
OF A MAGAZINE,

20:13.170 --> 20:15.172
AND THAT'S THE NAME OF THE GAME,
RIGHT?

20:17.549 --> 20:20.093
- OKAY,
ON A TECHNICALITY,

20:20.177 --> 20:24.890
A FILTHY, CRUSTY,
FUNGAL TECHNICALITY.

20:24.973 --> 20:26.767
- YEAH, I WON.
CROSS IF OFF, AND LET'S GO ON.

20:26.850 --> 20:28.644
- DON'T GET COCKY.

20:28.727 --> 20:30.771
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU'RE ACTUALLY
GOING TO GET WHEELS.

20:30.854 --> 20:33.523
- OH,
THEY'RE ALREADY IN MOTION, BABY.

20:33.607 --> 20:35.484
- IT'S A TOY CAR,
ISN'T IT?

20:35.567 --> 20:36.693
- [laughs]

20:36.777 --> 20:38.904
NO.

20:44.868 --> 20:46.578
- [shudders]

20:48.038 --> 20:50.415
- AND GATHER YOURSELF.

20:50.499 --> 20:52.000
YOU ARE THE RIVER.

20:52.084 --> 20:55.087
YOUR WORDS ARE THE SALMON.

20:55.170 --> 20:57.923
- FABIAN,
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

20:58.006 --> 20:59.424
- AND I NEED TO TALK TO YOU,
NINA.

20:59.508 --> 21:00.342
SIT.

21:00.425 --> 21:03.720
- DO AS THE BOY SAYS,
NINA.

21:05.597 --> 21:07.140
- OKAY, I OVERHEARD VICTOR
AND MR. SWEET TALKING--

21:07.224 --> 21:09.893
- NO,
TELL ME LATER.

21:09.977 --> 21:12.270
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

21:12.354 --> 21:15.023
- UM, I WANT TO
READ YOU SOMETHING FIRST.

21:15.107 --> 21:16.024
- TELL YOU LATER?

21:16.108 --> 21:18.110
FABIAN,
THIS IS LIFE-AND-DEATH STUFF.

21:18.193 --> 21:19.903
- NINA,
I AM GOING TO READ YOU THIS,

21:19.987 --> 21:21.863
AND YOU ARE GOING TO LISTEN.

21:21.947 --> 21:22.948
NOW, SIT.

21:23.031 --> 21:25.283
- I'M NOT A DOG, FABIAN.

21:25.367 --> 21:25.701
- UH, NO, NO, NO.
NINA.

21:25.784 --> 21:28.036
NINA.

21:36.878 --> 21:40.841
- UH-OH,
SOUNDS A BIT FINAL.

21:40.924 --> 21:43.719
SORRY.

21:48.807 --> 21:49.266
- WHY ARE YOU HIDING FROM ME?

21:49.349 --> 21:51.351
- I'M NOT.

21:51.435 --> 21:52.644
LISTEN, VICTOR'S AFTER SOMETHING
CALLED THE BOOK OF ISIS,

21:52.728 --> 21:54.771
AND WE--

21:54.855 --> 21:56.148
- YOU CAN'T IGNORE ME FOREVER,
NINA.

21:56.231 --> 21:58.066
- WHO'S IGNORING YOU.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.776
I JUST HAVE SOMETHING IMPORTANT
TO TELL YOU.

21:59.860 --> 22:03.697
- I SAID,
YOU CAN'T IGNORE ME FOREVER.

22:03.780 --> 22:07.409
[dramatic music]

22:07.492 --> 22:07.909
- THE MASK IS CLOSE

22:07.993 --> 22:09.870
I FEEL IT.

22:09.953 --> 22:12.831
ASK THE ONE WHO KNOWS.
